FRENCH COUNTRY WINES-Red

Despite the fact that the French franc was 2312c as we went to press, American tourists will still, this summer, occupy the better hotels of Paris and the wonderful inns, relais, and sea- side resorts of the French countryside. What will they drink? In most instances, they will drink the local wines that are charming and excellent that are still obtainable at low cost. These ‘country wines’ make no pretense to greatness—each has its own personal message, its own charm, and combines beau- tifully with the local food specialties. They can still be enjoyed in America today at delightfully low cost—most at well under $3.00 the bottle. These wines are interesting—relevant to sum- mer living—and should be enjoyed as adventures in wine tasting.
